tive metadata configuration might involve reflecting on the class with `Class.forName` and checking `getDeclaredFields`. If there’s no direct reference, it’s possible the holder is in a test jar. So, it’s good to note that tests might only fail once the schema is built, but I should look into existing style assertions.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_JYEx6eKhbbShpx9zccGme35I|fc_057e8b6594a86aa30169f3bccf36208194a57997dc1fa37094", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.apache.pekko/pekko-protobuf-v3_3/1.0.1/src/test/scala/org_apache_pekko/pekko_protobuf_v3_3/MessageSchemaTest.scala"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2019, "output": 1395, "cacheRead": 38912, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 42326, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777581239537, "responseId": "resp_057e8b6594a86aa30169f3bcb8a3f88194a7edcbd9ad4b78cf"}}
